Rating: 0
This was a wonderful recipe and a keeper, but you have to be careful not to let your caramel get too hot. I suggest a candy thermometer for those of you who had trouble with the caramel becoming hard crack. Sounds like you heated your caramel too high and too long. Don't let the caramel get too dark before putting it in the oven and you should have better results. Slower gentle bubbles will prove to give a softer consistency.

