I've made this twice but did not enjoy as much it the first time because I was in a hurry, careless, and forgot the skillet handle had been in a 400 degree oven when I was taking the pears out of the pan into bowls. Ouch. This is an exceptionally delicious dessert and so easy to prepare as long as you don't forget like I did. I had a plump organic lemon the second time so I zested it before squeezing it (why waste the zest?) and sprinkled on the zest when I put the pears into the oven. That made this superb dessert even better. Comice pears worked well too.

